		<published>2019-02-26T01:20:14+00:00</published>
		<id>https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=226045#p226045</id>
		<link href="https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=226045#p226045"/>
		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: LÖVE-Nuklear - a lightweight immediate mode GUI]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=226045#p226045"><![CDATA[
<blockquote class="uncited"><div>Hi keharriso, thanks a lot for all your work (binding and docs!). Just a question: how can I minimize a window at start, when I use ui:windowCollapse(mywindowname) once at start I can't expand it manually?</div></blockquote>Thanks for the kind words.<br><br>You need to keep track of whether or not the window has been collapsed yet or not. I did this in the following example with the "collapse" variable.<br><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>local collapse = truefunction love.update(dt)ui:frameBegin()if ui:windowBegin('Collapse Example', 100, 100, 200, 150,'border', 'title', 'movable', 'minimizable') thenui:layoutRow('dynamic', 30, 1)ui:label('Hello, world!')endui:windowEnd()if collapse thencollapse = falseui:windowCollapse('Collapse Example')endui:frameEnd()end</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=74528">keharriso</a> — Tue Feb 26, 2019 1:20 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
